rks/SAAC/README.md:5:This method only use **pretrained GPT2** and requires **no training**. In the original paper, only the first three sentences of the covertext is used as the context for conditional text generation. The secret bits are then fed to the text generation for stego-text.\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/GPT/README.md:5:First, finetune GPT-2 on covertext and stegotext, seperately. We then have 3 GPT-2 models:\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/GPT/README.md:7:* GPT-2 finetuned on covertext\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/GPT/README.md:8:* GPT-2 finetuned on stegotext\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/GPT/README.md:12:PPL of stegotext are evaluated:\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/GPT/README.md:13:* `PPL`: PPL of stegotext when generated.\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/GPT/README.md:19:Two types of JSD of stegotext are evaluated:\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/GPT/README.md:20:* `JSD-normal`: JSD of stegotext evaluated on the vanilla pretrained GPT-2 model\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/GPT/README.md:21:* `JSD-half`: JSD of stegotext evaluated on the Half-Half benchmark.\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/GPT/README.md:22:* `JSD-cover`: JSD of stegotext evaluated on the model finetuned on covertext\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/prior_works/NLS/README.md:5:This method only use **pretrained GPT2** and requires **no training**. In the original paper, only the first three sentences of the covertext is used as the context for conditional text generation. The secret bits are then fed to the text generation for stego-text.\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/steganalysis/README.md:3:This module is for stego analysis. It is used to evaluate the performance of steganography algorithms by applying classification methods.\ncode/zero-shot-GLS/evaluate/judge/README.md:3:We use ChatGPT to perform human-like judgement over the generated stego-text.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
